# Fix Text Box Cutoff Bug

## Goal
Prevent the text box in the active journal page from being cut off by the keyboard.

## Root Cause
The `SingleChildScrollView` in [_buildFieldPage](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/today_screen.dart#453-647) (and others) is set to `NeverScrollableScrollPhysics`, preventing the user from scrolling the content up when the viewport shrinks due to the keyboard appearance.

## Proposed Changes
### [lib/screens/today_screen.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/today_screen.dart)
- [MODIFY] In [_buildFieldPage](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/today_screen.dart#453-647), change the `physics` property of the `SingleChildScrollView` to be conditional.
    -   If `MediaQuery.of(context).viewInsets.bottom > 0` (Keyboard is open), use `BouncingScrollPhysics` (or default).
    -   Otherwise, keep `NeverScrollableScrollPhysics` to preserve the custom page-swipe gestures.

```dart
physics: MediaQuery.of(context).viewInsets.bottom > 0
    ? const BouncingScrollPhysics()
    : const NeverScrollableScrollPhysics(),
```

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
- Open the app and go to the "Today" screen.
- Tap on "What went well?" to focus the text field and open the keyboard.
- **Verify**: The view allows scrolling so the text field can be moved above the keyboard.
- **Verify**: When the keyboard is closed, the swipe-up/down gestures to switch prompts still work.
